==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bo tree
<hw>Bo" tree`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The peepul
tree; esp., the very ancient tree standing at Anurajahpoora in Ceylon,
grown from a slip of the tree under which Gautama is said to have
received the heavenly light and so to have become Buddha.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sacred <qex>bo tree</qex> of the Buddhists (<spn>Ficus
religiosa</spn>), which is planted close to every temple, and attracts
almost as much veneration as the status of the god himself. . . . It
differs from the banyan (<spn>Ficus Indica</spn>) by sending down no
roots from its branches.</q> <rj><qau>Tennent.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Botryogen</ent>⟦br⟧
